body:
This PR introduces a new task type, `index_parallel`, for parallel batch indexing without other systems like hadoop or spark. Here is a brief design overview.

- `index_parallel` task is a _supervisor task_. It basically creates multiple worker tasks and submits them to overlords. 
   - There are two reasons for adding a new supervisor task instead of a new supervisor. First, the supervisor is responsible for acquiring and releasing task locks, but our current locking system is tightly coupled with task system - a task should be submitted to acquire a lock. So, it is much easier to add a supervisor task rather than a supervisor. Second, our supervisor works greatly well, but it has the problem of single point of failure. Running a supervisor task on one of peons makes easier to avoid this problem by supporting retying failed supervisor tasks in the future.
- When a supervisor task is submitted, it first checks the given firehoseFactory is `splittable`. The splittable firehoseFactories are responsible for generating `inputSplit`s. The supervisor task will submit the same number of tasks with the number of inputSplits.
- Each worker task reads input data and makes segments. If everything goes well, they report a list of pushed segments via HTTP to the supervisor task.
- The supervisor task periodically checks the worker task statuses. If one of them fails, it resubmits the failed task until the retrying number reaches the configured limit. If all worker tasks succeed, then it collects the reported list of generated segments and publishes those segments.

Here is an example ingestion spec.

```
{
  "type" : "index_parallel",
  "spec" : {
    "ioConfig" : {
      "type" : "index_parallel",
      "firehose" : {
        "type" : "local",
        "baseDir" : "/some/path/to/wikiticker",
        "filter" : "*"
      }
    },
    "dataSchema" : {
      "dataSource" : "wikiticker",
      "granularitySpec" : {
        "type" : "uniform",
        "segmentGranularity" : "hour",
        "queryGranularity" : "hour",
        "intervals" : ["2015-09/2015-10"]
      },
      "parser" : {
        "type" : "hadoopyString",
        "parseSpec" : {
          "format" : "json",
          "dimensionsSpec" : {
            "dimensions" : [
              "channel",
              "cityName",
              "comment",
              "countryIsoCode",
              "countryName",
              "isAnonymous",
              "isMinor",
              "isNew",
              "isRobot",
              "isUnpatrolled",
              "metroCode",
              "namespace",
              "page",
              "regionIsoCode",
              "regionName",
              "user"
            ]
          },
          "timestampSpec" : {
            "format" : "auto",
            "column" : "time"
          }
        }
      },
      "metricsSpec" : [
        {
          "name" : "count",
          "type" : "count"
        },
        {
          "name" : "added",
          "type" : "longSum",
          "fieldName" : "added"
        },
        {
          "name" : "deleted",
          "type" : "longSum",
          "fieldName" : "deleted"
        },
        {
          "name" : "delta",
          "type" : "longSum",
          "fieldName" : "delta"
        },
        {
          "name" : "user_unique",
          "type" : "hyperUnique",
          "fieldName" : "user"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

This is based of proposal #5238. 
Introduces changes that support local batch indexing of data residing in RDBMS. A sample ingestion spec snippet would be as follows:

