        "type" : "map",
        "parseSpec" :
        	:
        	:

```
`SqlFirehoseFactory` is introduced which would execute the SQL query, read all the results to a file locally and index from the file. This avoids having to keep a persistent connection to the database until all the inputrows are read.
When prefetching is enabled and there are multiple sql queries to index from, the sql results are prefetched in the background similiar to PrefetchableTextFileFirehoseFactory.
Updated docs and added tests.
